raw_data.title: Computer Hardware Repair and Maintenance (post warranty)
raw_data.description: Installing hardware and software systems Troubleshooting a variety of computer issues Setting up computer security measures Configuring computer networks Offering technical support on-site or via phone or email or remote

raw_data.title: Cloud and Infrastructure Engineer
raw_data.description: Responsible for providing Cloud and IT business strategy, solution development and technical guidance to develop business and market solutions that align with cloud and it service offerings from the cloud service provider. Specializes in application and software architecture for Cloud IT and IT programs and activities.
raw_data.key_words: Cloud Strategy,Solution Development,Technical Guidance,Application Architecture,Software Architecture

raw_data.title: Cloud Engineer
raw_data.description: Design, implement, and manage cloud-based systems for businesses. They develop and implement cloud-applications, migrate existing on-premises applications to the cloud, and debug cloud stacks. Cloud architect is an IT specialist who develops computing strategies, which incorporates cloud adoption plans, application design and monitoring. Additional responsibilities include support for application architecture and deployment in cloud environments.

raw_data.title: Server Configuration and Maintenance Consultant
raw_data.description: 1. Engineering of SA-related solutions for various project and operational needs. 2. Install new / rebuild existing servers and configure hardware, peripherals, services, settings, directories, storage, etc. in accordance with standards and project/operationalrequirements. 3. Install and configure systems such as supports GIS infrastructure applications or Asset Management applications. 4. Develop and maintain installation and configuration procedures. 5. Contribute to and maintain system standards. 6. Research and recommend innovative, and where possible automated approaches for system administration tasks. Identify approaches that leverage our resources and provide economies of scale

raw_data.title: Network Administration Consultant
raw_data.description: WAN/LAN security assurance, install and configure routers, switches, and network components too ensure security standard is maintained. Also responsible for network security monitoring.

raw_data.title: Software Installation Consultant
raw_data.description: The Software engineer and Installer also called System Integration Engineer will interface with software and hardware components while also tracking changes made by the software development team and ensuring all security updates are integrated to produce a working set of systems. Relevant technologies include Microsoft Server 2008, SQL administration, Cloud solutions, and VMWare suite. The System Integration Engineer will be relied upon as an expert with in-depth technical knowledge of in software products while being a positive team player who can deliver quality enterprise grade solutions.

labor_categories.labor_category: Professional Services—Consulting and Integration, Cloud Solutions

raw_data.title: Professional Services—Consulting and Integration, Cloud Solutions
raw_data.description: Professional Services consultant is responsible fo the delivery of client specific business application customization, work together with System Integrator to deliver and deploy cloud and on premises solution, including but not limited to Office Web Apps, Microsoft Lync Online, Microsoft Exchange Online, Microsoft Dynamics CRM Online, Windows Server Active Directory, SharePoint Online, Office Live Meeting, Windows Intune, and VM Ware

raw_data.title: Help Desk Specialist
raw_data.description: Provides phone and in-person support to users in the areas of email, directories, standard Windows desktop applications, and applications developed under the contract. Serves as the initial point of contact for troubleshooting hardware/software PC and printer problems.

raw_data.title: Network Engineer
raw_data.description: Under general supervision analyzes local and wide area network systems (LAN/WANs), including planning, designing, evaluating, selecting operating systems and protocol suites and configuring communication media with concentrators, bridges and other devices.  Resolves interoperability problems to obtain operation across all platforms including e-mail, files transfer, multimedia, teleconferencing, etc.  Configures systems to user environments. Supports acquisition of hardware and software. Implements security concepts associated with this position.
raw_data.key_words: Network Engineer,IT Network Engineer,IT Engineer,Software Engineer,Hardware Engineer

raw_data.title: System Administrator
raw_data.description: System Administrator is charged with installing, supporting, and maintaining servers or other computer systems, and planning for and responding to service outages and other problems.  Other duties may include scripting or light programming, project management for systems-related projects, supervising or training computer operators, and being the consultant for computer problems beyond the knowledge of technical support staff.  Manages and executes security concepts associated with this position. Minimum Experience: 8 years relevant experience

raw_data.title: Security Engineer
raw_data.description: Security Engineers are responsible for the secure operations of cloud infrastructure, platforms, and software, including the installation, maintenance, and improvement of cloud computing environments. They also help develop new designs and security strategies across cloud-based applications, including infrastructure, platform, and SaaS.
